LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 267
BY WAYS AND MEANS COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO POWERS AND DUTIES OF BOARDS OF COMMISSIONERS; AMENDING SECTION
3 31-819, IDAHO CODE, TO REVISE PROVISIONS REGARDING PUBLICATION OF PRO-
4 CEEDINGS AND TO MAKE TECHNICAL CORRECTIONS; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY
5 AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
6 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
7 SECTION 1. That Section 31-819, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
8 amended to read as follows:
9 31-819. PUBLICATION OF PROCEEDINGS. (1) To The board of county commis-
10 sioners shall cause to be published monthly such statement as will clearly
11 give notice to the public of all its acts and proceedings, and, shall include
12 including a brief financial summary indicating the total amount spent from
13 each county fund during the month. A more detailed report of expenditures
14 may be published if deemed necessary by the board. Monthly publication of
15 acts and proceedings shall not be required for any county that maintains a
16 publicly accessible website on which agendas and minutes of the meetings of
17 the board of county commissioners are posted.
18 (2) Annually, a full financial report shall be prepared and available
19 for public inspection which that shows for each fund the sources of income,
20 expenditures during the year, current fund balances, and other financial in-
21 formation as determined by the board. Within thirty (30) days of the annual
22 audit's preparation as provided in section 31-1701, Idaho Code, the board
23 shall cause to be published a summary of the balance sheet and a summary of
24 the statement of revenues and expenditures. Such statements, as well as all
25 other public notices of proceedings of, or to be had before the board, not
26 otherwise specially provided for, must be published in accordance with the
27 requirements of chapter 1, title 60, Idaho Code.
28 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
29 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
30 July 1, 2025.

